<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910114-0046</DOCNO><DOCID>910114-0046.</DOCID><HL>   International Brief -- Ford Motor Co.:   British Operation Sets Plan   To Cut 900 Jobs This Year</HL><DATE>01/14/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   F</CO><IN>AUTOMOBILES (AUT)</IN><LP>   Ford Motor Co.'s British arm said it plans to trim staffby 900 in 1991 through voluntary means.   A spokesman said the anticipated cuts are part of aprogram of reducing staff and boosting efficiency.</LP><TEXT>   While the cuts will be spread over 10 Ford plants in theU.K., representing 2% of the company's current work force inBritain, the bulk of the reduction will come at plantsoutside London, the company said. From 250 to 300 cuts areanticipated at the Dagenham plant, while 500 to 600 cuts areexpected at the Hailsham plant, Ford said.   Ford said that over 20 years, U.K. staff levels have beenreduced to 44,000 from 65,000.</TEXT></DOC>